      • createChildAspect

        public Aspect createChildAspect()
        Description copied from interface: Aspect
        This method creates a child aspect, and returns it. This allows aspects to track information about Tang injection scopes. If such information is not needed, it is legal for Aspect implementations to return "this".
        Specified by:
        createChildAspect in interface Aspect

      • inject

        public <T> T inject(ConstructorDef<T> constructorDef,
           Constructor<T> constructor,
           Object[] args)
         throws InvocationTargetException,
                IllegalAccessException,
                IllegalArgumentException,
                InstantiationException
        Description copied from interface: Aspect
        Inject an object of type T.

        Note that it is never OK to return an instance of ExternalConstructor. Typical implementations check to see if they are about to return an instance of ExternalConstructor. If so, they return ret.newInstance() instead.

        Specified by:
        inject in interface Aspect
        Parameters:
        constructorDef - information about the constructor to be invoked. This is mostly useful because it contains references to any relevant named parameters, and to the class to be injected.
        constructor - The java constructor to be injected. Tang automatically chooses the appropriate constructor and ensures that we have permission to invoke it.
        args - The parameters to be passed into constructor.newInstance(), in the correct order.
        Returns:
        A new instance of T. Note, it is inject()'s responsibility to call ret.getInstance() if ret instanceof ExternalConstructor.
        Throws:
        InvocationTargetException
        IllegalAccessException
        IllegalArgumentException
        InstantiationException

      • injectionFutureInstantiated

        public <T> void injectionFutureInstantiated(InjectionFuture<T> arg0,
                                   T arg1)
        Description copied from interface: Aspect
        TANG calls this the first time get() is called on an injection future. This informs the aspect of the relationship between InjectionFutures (that were already passed into inject()) and the instantiated object.
        Specified by:
        injectionFutureInstantiated in interface Aspect
        Parameters:
        arg0 - An InjectionFuture that was passed to the args[] array of inject at some point in the past.
        arg1 - An object instance that was returned by inject().
